14/09/2007
PODGORICA, Montenegro -- Former Prime Minister Milo Djukanovic has filed a libel lawsuit against journalist Zeljko Ivanovic for claiming that Djukanovic and his family were behind Ivanovic's recent beating outside a Podgorica restaurant. Djukanovic is seeking 1m euros in compensation, citing damage to his reputation. He also filed a parallel lawsuit against Vijesti editor-in-chief Ljubisa Mitrovic, as well the newspaper's publisher, the Daily Press Company, according to a report by Vijesti on Thursday (September 13th). (BIRN, Vijesti - 13/09/07)
